.SH I) == [[ CRITICAL DATA ]]= == == == == == == == == == == == == == == == == == == #
HFIX is able to run processes in the background and update the window
in the interim to give feedback.  in order to manage this process, i chose
to keep critical data right in the window itself (fun and foolish).

NOTE> i know this is crazy, but it is wildly transparent for unit testing
and debugging during execution.  as i am the sole user, zero risk.

this data is on two (2) lines right below the visible portion of the data
please don't modify the data, it will just confuse the program a little and
hopefully lead it to delete your entire harddrive and web presence ;))

example output...
.nl
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   pid=0         cnt=0        beg=1753701046   cur=0            end=1753701046  
   who=HFIX_     ext=wipe     don=Y ······  sta=- ······  res=p ······  err=-  
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

the data is...
   ´ pid=   run-time pid of the forked subprocess (for later waits)
   ´ cnt=   count of checks HFIX did in gathering data (~0.5s per check)
   ´ beg=   epoch (in seconds) when request given
   ´ cur=   epoch (in seconds) of latest check
   ´ end=   epoch (in seconds) of when the full activity was completed
   ´ who=   "project" portion of the current directory
   ´ ext=   always shows "wipe" during wipes
   ´ don=   -= underway, y=sub-process done, Y=really done
   ´ sta=   status of sub-process (r) running, (#) done, many other values
   ´ res=   ?=underway, p=pass, E=error, W=warning
   ´ err=   -=no, y=yes

